text.__SUMMARY__: Prunus kinabaluensis is a species of plant in the family Rosaceae. It is found in Malaysia and the Philippines.
text.Sources: Kalkman, C. (1998). "Prunus kinabaluensis". The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. IUCN. 1998: e.T34612A9878083. doi:10.2305/IUCN.UK.1998.RLTS.T34612A9878083.en. Retrieved 22 December 2017.
